## Automated Update Script Safeguards
- The user's production environment strictly relies on a TrueNAS cron job targeting [update.sh](file:///d:/My%20Documents/Documents/3D%20Printing/Filament%20Command%20Center/update.sh) to execute git pulls and `midclt` restart sequences.
- **Spoolman DB Safeguard:** Hooked a new block natively into the bash update hook that evaluates [config.json](file:///d:/My%20Documents/Documents/3D%20Printing/Filament%20Command%20Center/config.json) via a one-line Python script, maps the Spoolman server IP organically, and drops a strict `curl -sSf` POST request natively against Spoolman's API-level Backup generation endpoint. 
- **Graceful Failure & Alerting:** If `curl` reads a non-200 code (signifying the Spoolman backup failed), [update.sh](file:///d:/My%20Documents/Documents/3D%20Printing/Filament%20Command%20Center/update.sh) immediately intercepts the error, bypasses the Git code pull, triggers `exit 1` to safeguard the environment against touching bad databases, and uses TrueNAS's `midclt call mail.send` API stack to dispatch an urgent administrator email directly highlighting the backup failure and manual intervention requirements.
- **Migrations Automation:** The script physically executes the [setup_fields.py](file:///d:/My%20Documents/Documents/3D%20Printing/Filament%20Command%20Center/setup-and-rebuild/setup_fields.py) schema injection and [migrate_spool_links.py](file:///d:/My%20Documents/Documents/3D%20Printing/Filament%20Command%20Center/setup-and-rebuild/migrate_spool_links.py) database sweep using Python 3 after successfully completing the `git reset --hard` but immediately *before* executing the TrueNAS `app.start` API wrapper. This comprehensively ensures that when code logically relies on new data nodes like `product_url`, they organically exist in the physical Docker runtime.
